aiken/interval/IntervalBound$Int.title: IntervalBound
aiken/interval/IntervalBound$Int.description: An interval bound, either inclusive or exclusive.

aiken/interval/IntervalBoundType$Int.title: IntervalBoundType
aiken/interval/IntervalBoundType$Int.description:
A type of interval bound. Where finite, a value of type `a` must be
 provided. `a` will typically be an `Int`, representing a number of seconds or
 milliseconds.

aiken_design_patterns/linked_list/ordere.title: NodeDatum
aiken_design_patterns/linked_list/ordere.description:
Every list node utxo:
 - has a unique `key` (unless it's the root node)
 - has a unique `link` to another node's key 
   (unless it's the last node of the list)
 - holds some app-specific `data`
